A = \begin{bmatrix}2 & 1 \\ -2 & 5\end{bmatrix}
D= \begin{bmatrix}4 & 0 \\ 0 & 3\end{bmatrix}
D=(P^{-1})AP
\therefore PD=AP
P=\begin{bmatrix} p & q \\ r & s\end{bmatrix}
\therefore \begin{bmatrix} p & q \\ r & s\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}4 & 0 \\ 0 & 3\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}2 & 1 \\ -2 & 5\end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix} p & q \\ r & s\end{bmatrix}
\iff\begin{bmatrix}4p & 3q \\ 4 r & 3s\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}2p + r & 2q+s\\-2p+5r & -2q+5s\end{bmatrix}
\iff\begin{cases}\begin{align}2p&=r\\q &=s\end{align} \end{cases}
\therefore P=\begin{bmatrix}p & q \\ 2 p & q\end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}1 & 0 \\ 2 & 0\end{bmatrix}p+\begin{bmatrix}0 & 1 \\ 0 & 1\end{bmatrix}q
P^{-1} = \begin{bmatrix}-\frac 1 p & \frac 1 p \\ \frac 2 q & - \frac 1 q\end{bmatrix}
